387
00:18:40,240 --> 00:18:41,700
I'll leave it here for now.

388
00:18:42,790 --> 00:18:43,790
This is nice.

389
00:18:43,900 --> 00:18:46,360
You should've given me something like this.

390
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:47,310
What do the words carved on it

391
00:18:47,310 --> 00:18:48,090
mean?

392
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:54,600
"As steadfast as a snow-capped mountain."

393
00:19:03,140 --> 00:19:03,670
Let's go?

394
00:19:04,380 --> 00:19:04,880
Go.

395
00:20:27,420 --> 00:20:28,330
Maybe

396
00:20:28,980 --> 00:20:29,840
some of you here

397
00:20:29,850 --> 00:20:31,110
have heard of me before

398
00:20:31,510 --> 00:20:33,110
and have some idea of who I am.

399
00:20:34,590 --> 00:20:35,520
I'm very nervous

400
00:20:37,530 --> 00:20:38,310
because I might not be

401
00:20:38,310 --> 00:20:39,330
who

402
00:20:39,980 --> 00:20:41,570
you expected.

403
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:44,810
Actually,

404
00:20:45,750 --> 00:20:47,550
my Mountain Patrol members and I

405
00:20:48,010 --> 00:20:49,210
are ordinary people.

406
00:20:50,550 --> 00:20:51,220
We are not

407
00:20:51,310 --> 00:20:52,640
some legendary heroes,

408
00:20:54,250 --> 00:20:55,850
nor are we immortal gods

409
00:20:56,700 --> 00:20:57,880
who can't be killed.

410
00:21:00,140 --> 00:21:02,400
Otherwise, I wouldn't be the only one...

411
00:21:04,290 --> 00:21:05,920
sitting here today.

412
00:21:07,380 --> 00:21:08,910
-Pull it over there.
-Okay.

413
00:21:10,700 --> 00:21:11,880
Our deputy captain,

414
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:13,730
Comrade He Qingyuan...

415
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:15,400
Okay. Pull it tighter.

416
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:16,050
Just sacrificed his life

417
00:21:16,050 --> 00:21:17,030
in a battle

418
00:21:18,310 --> 00:21:19,200
not long ago.

419
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:22,790
The reason we've been able to

420
00:21:22,790 --> 00:21:24,050
keep going until today

421
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:27,880
is that we can endure more hardship.

422
00:21:29,510 --> 00:21:30,250
We love

423
00:21:30,350 --> 00:21:31,210
this land more.

424
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:36,420
Seeing the corpses of Tibetan antelopes

425
00:21:36,420 --> 00:21:37,290
scattered throughout

426
00:21:37,290 --> 00:21:38,550
the Uninhabited Zone,

427
00:21:40,680 --> 00:21:41,440
we were just doing

428
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:42,640
what ordinary people

429
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:44,460
should do.

430
00:22:04,350 --> 00:22:04,940
Let's go.

431
00:22:05,250 --> 00:22:05,740
Okay.

432
00:22:06,590 --> 00:22:07,480
Sangba!

433
00:22:08,290 --> 00:22:09,020
We should go!

434
00:22:09,510 --> 00:22:10,770
Alright! Almost done!

435
00:22:27,510 --> 00:22:28,510
County Mayor Lin!

436
00:22:28,830 --> 00:22:29,790
What's the rush?

437
00:22:29,880 --> 00:22:30,510
Secretary Chen has called

438
00:22:30,510 --> 00:22:31,570
an emergency meeting

439
00:22:31,570 --> 00:22:33,180
and asked you to come over right away.

440
00:22:33,180 --> 00:22:34,240
A baby Tibetan antelope

441
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:35,310
can run faster

442
00:22:36,180 --> 00:22:37,710
three days after it's born!

443
00:22:38,740 --> 00:22:40,200
But it still can't outrun

444
00:22:40,960 --> 00:22:42,140
the poachers' jeeps

445
00:22:42,240 --> 00:22:42,970
and bullets.

446
00:22:44,570 --> 00:22:45,630
In just a few years,

447
00:22:46,380 --> 00:22:48,850
the Tibetan antelope population has been hunted down

448
00:22:48,850 --> 00:22:50,450
from 200,000 to only 30,000.

449
00:22:55,850 --> 00:22:56,780
These photos...

450
00:22:58,680 --> 00:22:59,540
and this one...

451
00:23:00,900 --> 00:23:01,830
are all evidence

452
00:23:01,900 --> 00:23:03,220
we took at the scene...

453
00:23:05,030 --> 00:23:06,430
of the poachers shooting

454
00:23:06,460 --> 00:23:07,790
and killing antelopes.

455
00:23:08,480 --> 00:23:09,500
But Mazhi County is

456
00:23:09,500 --> 00:23:11,100
a poverty-stricken county.

457
00:23:11,960 --> 00:23:13,240
It's hard to get paid.

458
00:23:13,790 --> 00:23:15,200
let alone provide much funding

459
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:15,980
for us to protect

460
00:23:15,980 --> 00:23:16,790
wild animals.

461
00:23:18,110 --> 00:23:19,510
It's already remarkable that the county

462
00:23:19,510 --> 00:23:20,550
could support us

463
00:23:20,640 --> 00:23:22,770
in establishing the Mountain Patrol.

464
00:23:24,640 --> 00:23:25,610
Many times,

465
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:27,680
my team members and I

466
00:23:27,680 --> 00:23:28,550
ate

467
00:23:29,350 --> 00:23:31,460
frozen tsampa and dried meat

468
00:23:32,310 --> 00:23:33,440
and drank snow water

469
00:23:34,030 --> 00:23:35,960
while chasing poachers out there.

470
00:23:36,570 --> 00:23:38,460
The Municipal Discipline Inspection Commission

471
00:23:38,460 --> 00:23:39,550
just forwarded a letter

472
00:23:39,550 --> 00:23:40,480
from the public.

473
00:23:40,880 --> 00:23:42,160
Everyone, take a look.

474
00:24:14,850 --> 00:24:15,250
Chief.

475
00:24:15,330 --> 00:24:17,750
Turn off the engine. All of you, get out of the car.

476
00:24:17,750 --> 00:24:18,240
Chief,

477
00:24:18,920 --> 00:24:19,780
what happened?

478
00:24:19,830 --> 00:24:21,090
People might consider

479
00:24:21,900 --> 00:24:22,900
some of my methods

480
00:24:22,940 --> 00:24:23,880
radical.

481
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:26,220
Well, I can't help it.

482
00:24:28,030 --> 00:24:29,660
We had no other choice!

483
00:24:30,220 --> 00:24:31,310
We could only do it!

484
00:24:33,180 --> 00:24:34,710
If we keep working like this

485
00:24:35,480 --> 00:24:37,240
and can make even a small contribution

486
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:39,370
to humanity and society in the future,

487
00:24:39,530 --> 00:24:40,770
I think it's worth it!

488
00:25:00,750 --> 00:25:02,270
Members of the Mountain Patrol

489
00:25:02,270 --> 00:25:03,220
are suspected of

490
00:25:03,310 --> 00:25:05,110
trafficking wildlife products

491
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:08,070
and illegally trading firearms and ammunition.

492
00:25:08,070 --> 00:25:09,530
All of you, come back to the station

493
00:25:09,530 --> 00:25:10,930
with me for questioning.

494
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:14,310
Chief.

495
00:25:15,350 --> 00:25:16,480
That's impossible.

496
00:25:17,350 --> 00:25:18,000
How could we possibly

497
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:19,000
do such things?

498
00:25:20,460 --> 00:25:21,320
Follow orders.

499
00:25:21,640 --> 00:25:22,700
Take them all away!

500
00:25:22,830 --> 00:25:23,160
Move.

501
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:23,850
Move.

502
00:25:23,980 --> 00:25:25,310
We are Forestry Police!

503
00:25:25,700 --> 00:25:26,880
Police arresting police?

504
00:25:26,880 --> 00:25:28,010
Move! Get in the car!

505
00:25:28,030 --> 00:25:28,440
Get in!

506
00:25:30,160 --> 00:25:30,490
Move!

507
00:25:31,680 --> 00:25:32,350
Chief!

508
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:35,000
County Mayor Duo.

509
00:25:36,050 --> 00:25:38,140
I just received payment for my article.

510
00:25:38,140 --> 00:25:39,220
I'd like to ask you, County Mayor Duo,

511
00:25:39,220 --> 00:25:40,200
to accept it.

512
00:25:41,310 --> 00:25:42,840
I don't know if it's enough.

513
00:25:42,940 --> 00:25:43,700
First,

514
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:45,270
please buy a khata

515
00:25:45,700 --> 00:25:47,630
and offer it to our fallen comrade.

516
00:25:47,880 --> 00:25:49,030
With the rest,

517
00:25:49,480 --> 00:25:51,280
buy whatever supplies you need.

518
00:25:54,510 --> 00:25:55,110
Thank you.

519
00:26:04,960 --> 00:26:05,490
Your gun.

520
00:26:31,310 --> 00:26:32,110
Take her away.

521
00:26:36,550 --> 00:26:37,220
Mainly,

522
00:26:37,310 --> 00:26:38,090
I think the outside world

523
00:26:38,090 --> 00:26:38,680
doesn't understand us enough.

524
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:39,410
Okay, got it.

525
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:40,500
So I also hope that

526
00:26:40,500 --> 00:26:41,240
if you ever have time,

527
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:42,110
you can come to my hometown

528
00:26:42,110 --> 00:26:42,970
and take a look.

529
00:26:43,380 --> 00:26:44,460
You can see, um...

530
00:26:44,550 --> 00:26:45,180
Excuse me.

531
00:26:45,270 --> 00:26:46,110
Excuse me, everyone.

532
00:26:46,110 --> 00:26:47,140
I want to speak with Captain Duojie

533
00:26:47,140 --> 00:26:48,000
for a moment.

534
00:26:48,770 --> 00:26:49,310
Okay.

535
00:26:50,700 --> 00:26:53,160
Something happened to the Mountain Patrol.

536
00:26:55,770 --> 00:26:56,920
Last November,

537
00:26:57,290 --> 00:26:58,010
you sold

538
00:26:58,110 --> 00:26:58,940
120 Tibetan antelope pelts

539
00:26:58,940 --> 00:27:00,070
on the black market.

540
00:27:00,570 --> 00:27:01,420
Is that true?

541
00:27:01,770 --> 00:27:02,700
Impossible!

542
00:27:03,830 --> 00:27:04,830
To raise money,

543
00:27:05,250 --> 00:27:05,960
Captain Duojie

544
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:07,760
even mortgaged his own pasture!

545
00:27:08,110 --> 00:27:08,790
How could we possibly

546
00:27:08,790 --> 00:27:09,700
sell pelts?

547
00:27:11,510 --> 00:27:12,240
We did.

548
00:27:14,460 --> 00:27:15,790
That was the first time.

549
00:27:19,070 --> 00:27:20,090
At that time, our deputy captain,

550
00:27:20,090 --> 00:27:20,980
He Qingyuan...

551
00:27:22,680 --> 00:27:24,480
was shot in the Uninhabited Zone

552
00:27:25,510 --> 00:27:27,910
and desperately needed money for surgery.

553
00:27:28,070 --> 00:27:29,270
There were also team members

554
00:27:29,270 --> 00:27:31,730
waiting for rescue in the Uninhabited Zone.

555
00:27:32,250 --> 00:27:33,420
We needed to buy supplies

556
00:27:33,420 --> 00:27:34,620
and get in there fast.

557
00:27:35,310 --> 00:27:36,570
We really had no money.

558
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:40,000
How many times did you sell pelts in total?

559
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:40,590
Three.

560
00:27:41,140 --> 00:27:42,000
Who ordered it?

561
00:28:09,680 --> 00:28:11,030
According to the report,

562
00:28:11,030 --> 00:28:11,660
the money

563
00:28:11,750 --> 00:28:13,280
from the third sale of pelts

564
00:28:13,330 --> 00:28:13,750
was also used

565
00:28:13,750 --> 00:28:15,510
to purchase firearms and ammunition.

566
00:28:15,510 --> 00:28:16,420
Is that true?

567
00:28:18,900 --> 00:28:19,440
Yes.

568
00:28:20,010 --> 00:28:21,340
What were they used for?

569
00:28:21,510 --> 00:28:22,510
At Mount Qimar,

570
00:28:22,940 --> 00:28:24,240
the illegal gold miners

571
00:28:24,240 --> 00:28:25,170
had lots of guns.

572
00:28:26,180 --> 00:28:27,480
The guns and ammo the Public Security Bureau gave us

573
00:28:27,480 --> 00:28:28,410
weren't enough.

574
00:28:29,400 --> 00:28:31,030
We had to make some preparations.

575
00:28:31,030 --> 00:28:32,830
Who arranged the deal this time?

576
00:28:34,900 --> 00:28:35,720
Me.

577
00:28:36,440 --> 00:28:37,010
Did you know about

578
00:28:37,010 --> 00:28:37,810
all of this?

579
00:28:46,850 --> 00:28:47,580
No, I didn't.

580
00:31:07,030 --> 00:31:08,110
Why did you come?

581
00:31:10,310 --> 00:31:11,510
Where is the Captain?

582
00:31:13,180 --> 00:31:14,310
Was he arrested too?

583
00:31:20,350 --> 00:31:21,310
Say something.

584
00:31:23,940 --> 00:31:24,530
Tell me.

585
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:26,040
After you got in trouble,

586
00:31:27,270 --> 00:31:28,030
he immediately rushed back

587
00:31:28,030 --> 00:31:29,290
from Beijing.

588
00:31:31,700 --> 00:31:33,700
But on the way back from the airport,

589
00:31:36,460 --> 00:31:37,390
he disappeared.

590
00:31:43,420 --> 00:31:44,550
He disappeared?

591
00:31:46,980 --> 00:31:49,180
Some people in the county are saying...

592
00:31:50,590 --> 00:31:52,250
he fled to escape punishment.

593
00:31:55,660 --> 00:31:56,850
County Mayor Lin is busy right now.

594
00:31:56,850 --> 00:31:57,510
Let me in!

595
00:31:57,640 --> 00:31:58,310
Miss Bai,

596
00:31:59,110 --> 00:31:59,680
he is busy.

597
00:31:59,680 --> 00:32:00,550
I'll just say a few words!

598
00:32:00,550 --> 00:32:00,980
Miss Bai!

599
00:32:00,980 --> 00:32:01,270
Let me in!

600
00:32:01,270 --> 00:32:01,570
Miss Bai!

601
00:32:01,570 --> 00:32:01,880
Let me in!

602
00:32:01,880 --> 00:32:02,420
He is busy!

603
00:32:02,420 --> 00:32:03,030
Miss Bai!

604
00:32:03,140 --> 00:32:03,680
Miss Bai...

605
00:32:03,680 --> 00:32:04,680
County Mayor Lin,

606
00:32:04,680 --> 00:32:06,090
I want to talk to you!

607
00:32:08,030 --> 00:32:08,460
Okay.

608
00:32:08,570 --> 00:32:09,900
Zhang, you may leave us.

609
00:32:17,960 --> 00:32:18,960
County Mayor Lin,

610
00:32:19,750 --> 00:32:20,350
why do you say

611
00:32:20,350 --> 00:32:22,280
Duojie fled to escape punishment?

612
00:32:25,110 --> 00:32:27,310
The case is still under investigation.

613
00:32:27,440 --> 00:32:28,240
We are looking for him too.

614
00:32:28,240 --> 00:32:29,500
He couldn't have fled!

615
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:32,270
The gold mine has been sealed off,

616
00:32:32,270 --> 00:32:33,070
and the Mountain Patrol has attracted

617
00:32:33,070 --> 00:32:34,180
so much attention.

618
00:32:34,830 --> 00:32:35,750
He was even planning

619
00:32:35,750 --> 00:32:37,110
to establish a reserve.

620
00:32:38,010 --> 00:32:39,010
He just received so much support

621
00:32:39,010 --> 00:32:40,400
in Beijing!

622
00:32:40,770 --> 00:32:41,740
He couldn't have just

623
00:32:41,740 --> 00:32:42,480
left the Mountain Patrol behind

624
00:32:42,480 --> 00:32:43,330
like this!

625
00:32:47,010 --> 00:32:47,940
Then...

626
00:32:49,090 --> 00:32:50,290
where is he right now?

627
00:32:56,310 --> 00:32:57,050
The county has mobilized

628
00:32:57,050 --> 00:32:59,110
almost everyone these past few days,

629
00:32:59,550 --> 00:33:00,400
contacting all of Duojie's relatives

630
00:33:00,400 --> 00:33:01,250
and friends.

631
00:33:03,500 --> 00:33:05,010
The County Public Security Bureau

632
00:33:05,010 --> 00:33:06,070
is also conducting searches

633
00:33:06,070 --> 00:33:06,810
along the road from the airport

634
00:33:06,810 --> 00:33:07,610
to the county.

635
00:33:12,350 --> 00:33:14,150
I've known him for so many years.

636
00:33:15,380 --> 00:33:15,710
I know

637
00:33:15,720 --> 00:33:17,050
no matter what happens,

638
00:33:18,550 --> 00:33:19,350
Duojie is a man

639
00:33:19,350 --> 00:33:20,810
who owns up to his actions.

640
00:33:21,700 --> 00:33:22,900
He would never hide just because of

641
00:33:22,900 --> 00:33:24,100
something like this.

642
00:33:26,160 --> 00:33:27,290
You don't want this,

643
00:33:27,940 --> 00:33:28,960
and I want it even less for Duojie

644
00:33:28,960 --> 00:33:30,490
to end up in this situation.

645
00:33:38,140 --> 00:33:40,340
But you did sell Tibetan antelope pelts

646
00:33:40,460 --> 00:33:41,830
and illegally

647
00:33:43,140 --> 00:33:44,610
purchase guns.

648
00:33:44,700 --> 00:33:46,420
Is that entirely our fault?

649
00:33:48,750 --> 00:33:50,350
We only earn 200 yuan a month,

650
00:33:51,200 --> 00:33:53,060
and we often go unpaid for months.

651
00:33:53,530 --> 00:33:54,070
Usually, we just eat

652
00:33:54,070 --> 00:33:56,670
plain noodle soup, with no meat or vegetables.

653
00:33:56,770 --> 00:33:58,700
When we face poachers in the mountains,

654
00:33:58,700 --> 00:33:59,180
they have

655
00:33:59,180 --> 00:34:00,030
loads of guns

656
00:34:00,140 --> 00:34:01,140
and ammunition!

657
00:34:02,090 --> 00:34:03,070
Our team member was injured

658
00:34:03,070 --> 00:34:04,330
and nearly lost a limb!

659
00:34:04,940 --> 00:34:05,680
We barely scraped together

660
00:34:05,680 --> 00:34:07,140
the money for the surgery!

661
00:34:09,320 --> 00:34:10,920
In our most difficult times,

662
00:34:11,940 --> 00:34:13,010
Duojie even had to

663
00:34:13,110 --> 00:34:14,150
mortgage his own pasture

664
00:34:14,150 --> 00:34:14,940
just to cover

665
00:34:15,030 --> 00:34:15,960
our gas money!

666
00:34:16,500 --> 00:34:17,280
The funding allocated to us

667
00:34:17,280 --> 00:34:18,940
was taken away just like that!

668
00:34:19,320 --> 00:34:20,650
The herdsmen's livestock matter,

669
00:34:20,650 --> 00:34:20,880
but

670
00:34:20,980 --> 00:34:22,570
we don't?

671
00:34:23,960 --> 00:34:25,820
"Fleeing to escape punishment?"

672
00:34:27,780 --> 00:34:29,070
Why would he flee?

673
00:34:31,050 --> 00:34:32,500
What crime did he commit?

674
00:34:45,010 --> 00:34:46,000
Uncle Lin...

675
00:34:52,260 --> 00:34:53,590
Please help us.

676
00:34:57,440 --> 00:34:58,840
Please help us.

677
00:35:07,820 --> 00:35:09,280
I understand how you feel.

678
00:35:11,440 --> 00:35:13,100
I'm just as anxious as you are.

679
00:35:16,010 --> 00:35:16,500
But right now,

680
00:35:16,500 --> 00:35:17,830
we still can't find him.

681
00:35:19,190 --> 00:35:19,860
And without him, a lot of things

682
00:35:19,860 --> 00:35:21,720
just can't be explained clearly.

683
00:35:28,130 --> 00:35:28,920
I hope...

684
00:35:32,340 --> 00:35:33,800
I hope you can understand.

685
00:35:39,570 --> 00:35:40,700
I can't understand.

686
00:35:41,690 --> 00:35:43,400
After discussion and approval

687
00:35:43,400 --> 00:35:44,550
by the Party branch meeting

688
00:35:44,550 --> 00:35:46,670
of the Mazhi County Public Security Bureau

689
00:35:46,670 --> 00:35:48,630
and with the consent of the Bureau Party Committee,

690
00:35:48,630 --> 00:35:50,630
it was decided to give Comrade Bai Ju

691
00:35:50,900 --> 00:35:52,480
a Party warning.

692
00:35:53,300 --> 00:35:53,960
Comrade Bai Ju

693
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:55,090
must properly accept

694
00:35:55,090 --> 00:35:56,210
the organization's decision

695
00:35:56,210 --> 00:35:58,270
and reflect deeply on her own issues.

696
00:36:28,420 --> 00:36:30,150
As a Communist Party member...

697
00:36:31,570 --> 00:36:33,630
one must still seek truth from facts.

698
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:40,400
What about Duojie's report?

699
00:36:57,010 --> 00:36:58,140
My suggestion is...

700
00:37:01,710 --> 00:37:03,710
to submit both application reports

701
00:37:03,730 --> 00:37:04,510
together.

702
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:07,670
I agree.

703
00:37:43,190 --> 00:37:43,960
Well...

704
00:37:46,260 --> 00:37:47,000
how will the newspaper office

705
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:48,260
deal with me this time?

706
00:37:54,960 --> 00:37:55,560
Forget it.

707
00:37:55,650 --> 00:37:57,250
Whatever happens, happens.

708
00:37:59,880 --> 00:38:00,800
Tell me...

709
00:38:02,960 --> 00:38:03,980
If back then,

710
00:38:05,570 --> 00:38:06,280
I'd really seen them

711
00:38:06,280 --> 00:38:07,420
selling pelts,

712
00:38:09,340 --> 00:38:11,400
do you think I would've stopped them?

713
00:38:17,380 --> 00:38:18,360
If it were me...

714
00:38:21,880 --> 00:38:22,810
I couldn't have.

715
00:38:32,860 --> 00:38:33,840
I guess...

716
00:38:35,760 --> 00:38:36,730
this time,

717
00:38:36,860 --> 00:38:39,120
whether I get transferred or suspended,

718
00:38:40,230 --> 00:38:41,530
it'll be over in a week or two

719
00:38:41,530 --> 00:38:42,690
at most.

720
00:38:44,110 --> 00:38:45,840
At worst, I'll just lose my job.

721
00:38:46,210 --> 00:38:47,610
Doesn't matter anymore.

722
00:38:49,880 --> 00:38:51,540
I'll come back as soon as I can.

723
00:38:51,980 --> 00:38:53,510
You don't need to come back.

724
00:38:56,090 --> 00:38:58,150
There is no Mountain Patrol anymore.

725
00:38:59,610 --> 00:39:00,940
The Captain is missing.

726
00:39:03,030 --> 00:39:03,760
This path

727
00:39:05,340 --> 00:39:05,940
is cut off.

728
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:10,500
You never belonged here.

729
00:39:13,500 --> 00:39:15,030
You don't need to come back.

730
00:39:15,380 --> 00:39:16,510
Bai Ju, I don't care.

731
00:39:17,550 --> 00:39:18,650
I don't care at all!

732
00:39:21,630 --> 00:39:22,630
The Captain hasn't been found yet.

733
00:39:22,630 --> 00:39:23,070
And...

734
00:39:25,650 --> 00:39:26,480
And you're still here.

735
00:39:26,480 --> 00:39:27,150
I definitely can't...

736
00:39:27,150 --> 00:39:27,840
You can't help with

737
00:39:27,840 --> 00:39:29,300
the Captain's situation.

738
00:39:32,590 --> 00:39:33,480
As for me...

739
00:39:36,940 --> 00:39:38,230
even I don't know

740
00:39:39,460 --> 00:39:40,920
what my future looks like.

741
00:39:42,840 --> 00:39:44,500
So what could you possibly do?

742
00:39:49,230 --> 00:39:50,560
Stop talking nonsense.

743
00:39:52,150 --> 00:39:53,810
Care about yourself for once.

744
00:40:16,150 --> 00:40:17,750
A favor returned for a favor—

745
00:40:19,130 --> 00:40:19,940
that's

746
00:40:21,610 --> 00:40:22,860
how bonds are formed.

747
00:40:27,050 --> 00:40:27,800
Thank you.

748
00:40:31,550 --> 00:40:32,340
You said

749
00:40:33,920 --> 00:40:35,820
this book means

750
00:40:36,800 --> 00:40:38,000
a lot to you.

751
00:40:40,340 --> 00:40:41,050
So...

752
00:40:43,070 --> 00:40:44,530
it shouldn't belong here,

753
00:40:46,670 --> 00:40:48,000
and certainly not to me.

754
00:40:51,440 --> 00:40:53,040
It's time to return it to you.

755
00:41:09,590 --> 00:41:10,360
But there are some things

756
00:41:10,360 --> 00:41:11,560
I won't return to you.

757
00:41:14,340 --> 00:41:15,800
I'll keep them in my heart.

758
00:41:20,300 --> 00:41:21,510
For us...

759
00:41:24,460 --> 00:41:26,150
just keeping them in our hearts is enough.

